libbc-core (1.3.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat(memory): prepared byte-mask primitive for repeated short-range
    scans. New API :
      - bc_core_byte_mask_t (opaque 64-byte struct holding 4 nibble LUTs)
      - bc_core_byte_mask_prepare(targets, count, &mask)
      - bc_core_byte_mask_prepare_predicate(fn, user_data, &mask)
      - bc_core_find_byte_in_mask(data, len, &mask, &out_offset)
      - bc_core_find_byte_not_in_mask(data, len, &mask, &out_offset)
    AVX2 pshufb nibble-LUT, identical scan kernel to find_any_byte but
    the LUT build cost is paid once at prepare time. Targets lexers
    and protocol parsers where a stop-set is known upfront and the
    scan is invoked thousands of times per input.
  * The "not_in_mask" variant is symmetrical: returns the first byte
    NOT in the prepared set — useful for "run of identifier chars",
    "run of digits", "whitespace skip" without having to enumerate
    the complement set.
  * No breaking API change.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Wed, 22 Apr 2026 23:00:00 +0100

libbc-core (1.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add bc_core_ascii_lowercase(void*, size_t): AVX2 / SSE2 / scalar
    dispatch for in-place ASCII lowercase. Consumed by bc-count for
    pattern --ignore-case; generic primitive reusable by bc-text,
    bc-hrtl.
  * No breaking API change.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Wed, 22 Apr 2026 23:59:00 +0000

libbc-core (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add libFuzzer harness infrastructure under fuzzing/ (3 targets:
    hash, memory, search). Gated by -Dfuzzing=true and
    -fsanitize=fuzzer when CC=clang.
  * Fix shift-by-32 undefined behaviour in
    bc_core_count_lines_with_pattern when the AVX2 path computes
    1u << (newline_bit + 1) and newline_bit == 31. Cast to uint64
    before shifting. Found via libFuzzer, regression test added.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Wed, 22 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0000

libbc-core (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * Memory primitives: cache-line-aware copy/zero, SIMD equal/compare,
    NUL-bounded length, byte-find / last-byte-find.
  * Hash primitives: SHA-256 with runtime-dispatched SHA-NI fast path,
    CRC32C (Castagnoli) via SSE4.2.
  * Math primitives: overflow-safe add/multiply, clamp helpers.
  * CPU helpers: BC_UNUSED macro, CPUID feature-flag probes.
  * Full sanitizer coverage (asan / tsan / ubsan / memcheck) and
    cppcheck-clean sources.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 23:30:00 +0000
